$ System.Runtime.InteropServices.RuntimeEnvironment (class)

The `System.Runtime.InteropServices.RuntimeEnvironment` class contains a set of static methods that provide information about the
→ Microsoft/dot-net/Common-Language-Runtime[Common Language Runtime] Environment.

{ PowerShell

  In PowerShell, this information might be queried like so:
code {
PS C:\> [Runtime.InteropServices.RuntimeEnvironment]::SystemConfigurationFile   # Returns the location of the (system wide) → Windows/dirs/Windows/Microsoft_NET/Framework64/vn_n_n/Config/machine_config[machine.config] file
PS C:\> [Runtime.InteropServices.RuntimeEnvironment]::GetRuntimeDirectory()     # Directory where the CLR is installed.
PS C:\> [Runtime.InteropServices.RuntimeEnvironment]::GetSystemVersion()        # Version number of CLR that is is running the current process.
code }

}
{ FromGlobalaccessCache #FromGlobalaccessCache

`FromGlobalaccessCache` tests whether a given → Microsoft/dot-net/assembly is loaded into the → Microsoft/dot-net/assembly/Global-Assembly-Cache,
 see → Microsoft/dot-net/assembly/Global-Assembly-Cache#gac-test-assembly[this PowerShell script]

}
